There's [Multiset.Nodup.of_map](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/Multiset/Nodup.html#Multiset.Nodup.of_map) too.
And I wonder whether `âˆ€ x âˆˆ s, âˆ€ y âˆˆ s, f x = f y â†’ x = y` should be written as `Set.injOn f s` ...
This was to match the signature of `Nodup.map_on` and `inj_on_of_nodup_map` etc. Maybe we should change all of them instead. But maybe in another PR?
I also would prefer to defer this

```suggestion
  Quot.induction_on s fun _l => by simpa using List.nodup_iff_count_eq_one
```
if you want, or
```
  by rcases s; simp_rw [quot_mk_to_coe'', coe_count]; exact List.nodup_iff_count_eq_one
```
The actual non-defeq simp lemma used is `coe_count`, because [Multiset.countP](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/Multiset/Basic.html#Multiset.countP) uses `Prop` but [List.countP](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Std/Data/List/Basic.html#List.countP) uses `Bool`.
